   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>124 8.8.8.8.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Now we are resting in the Lamb</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Who can enough His love relate?</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Our gross offenses, countless sins,</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Banished by blood that cleared our slate.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>He paid the price for perfect peace,</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>We sing His praises all the day;</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Both God and man are satisfied,</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>For blood has washed our sins away.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The stains are gone oh, precious blood!</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Our conscience does not come between;</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Nor filth nor fault of sin is here,</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>For God has said that we are clean.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Now we are filled with such a peace;</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>We will go on, and not in fear:</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>We will know peace that's sweeter still,</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>And righteous at His side appear.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>125 8.8.6.8.8.6. with repeat.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Thou Son of God, our Savior dear,</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Through Thee redemption did appear,</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>From sin and death to free.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Thy saints Thy blessings do expound,</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Thou art with glory ever crowned,</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>And seated heavenly.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>And seated heavenly.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Love of the Father lifted Thee,</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Bestowed such power, majesty;</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Upon His right art Thou.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>We praise Thy wisdom, Sovereign true,</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>And consecrate our all anew;</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Thou reignest ever now.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Thou reignest ever now.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Head of the Church in righteousness,</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Thy members Thou didst fully bless:</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>All that Thou hast is ours.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Our life and power Thou become,</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>In all our motives, set Thy throne,</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>And conquer Satan's pow'rs.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>And conquer Satan's pow'rs.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Not long that glor'ous day shall come,</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Your Body will be raptured home,</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Ever to see Thy face.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Such happy day!</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Thyself to see,</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>And know that we belong to Thee,</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>And rest in Thine embrace.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>And rest in Thine embrace.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
